0train%20ChatGPT.%3Cp%3ECFOTO%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPublishers%20want%20compensation%20from%20OpenAI%20for%20using%20their%20works%20to%20train%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Center%20for%20Investigative%20Reporting%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20company%20this%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20and%20other%20outlets%20also%20have%20similar%20lawsuits%20against%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20uses%20any%20and%20all%20publicly%20available%20data%20to%20train%20ChatGPT%2C%20including%20books%20and%20articles%20from%20the%20internet.%20Now%2C%20those%20who%20own%20them%20want%20to%20be%20paid%20for%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-killing-web-grand-bargain-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETraining%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20creating%20the%20AI%20models%20that%20are%20taking%20over%20the%20tech%20world.%20Leading%20tech%20companies%20like%20Google%2C%20Meta%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20Anthropic%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20are%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-data-source-solutions-openai-meta-google-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escrambling%20to%20find%20new%20sources%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20data.%20Meta%20at%20one%20point%20even%20considered%20buying%20Simon%20%26amp%3B%20Schuster%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20biggest%20publishing%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20publishers%20are%20increasingly%20accusing%20these%20companies%20of%20hoovering%20up%20copyrighted%20data.%20They'd%20like%20to%20be%20paid%20for%20their%20work.%20Meta%20and%20OpenAI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-accuses-new-york-times-hiring-someone-hack-its-products-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20comments%20to%20the%20US%20Copyright%20Office%20that%20putting%20copyrighted%20material%20on%20the%20internet%20makes%20it%20%26quot%3Bpublicly%20available%26quot%3B%20and%20thus%20under%20fair%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they'll%20still%20have%20to%20make%20that%20argument%20in%20court%20as%20the%20company%20faces%20lawsuits%20from%20several%20groups%20over%20the%20copyrighted%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Center%20for%20Investigative%20Reporting%2C%20a%20news%20nonprofit%20known%20sometimes%20by%20its%20acronym%20CIR%20and%20which%20merged%20with%20Mother%20Jones%20and%20Reveal%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20sued%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%20last%20week%20in%20federal%20court.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.motherjones.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FCIR_Lawsuit_Against-OpenAI_06.27.24.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elawsuit%20accuses%3C%2Fa%3E%20OpenAI%20of%20being%20%26quot%3Bbuilt%20on%20the%20exploitation%20of%20copyrighted%20works%20belonging%20to%20creators%20around%20the%20world%2C%20including%20CIR.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20the%20CIR%20accused%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%20of%20using%20copyrighted%20material%20from%20Mother%20Jones%20to%20train%20their%20GPT%20and%20Copilot%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%20started%20vacuuming%20up%20our%20stories%20to%20make%20their%20product%20more%20powerful%2C%20but%20they%20never%20asked%20for%20permission%20or%20offered%20compensation%2C%20unlike%20other%20organizations%20that%20license%20our%20material%2C%26quot%3B%20Monika%20Bauerlein%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Investigative%20Reporting%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frevealnews.org%2Fpress%2Fcir-sues-openai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20an%20announcement%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20lawsuit.%20%26quot%3BThis%20free%20rider%20behavior%20is%20not%20only%20unfair%2C%20it%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20copyright.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20that%20%26quot%3B16%2C793%20distinct%20URLs%20from%20Mother%20Jones's%20web%20domain%26quot%3B%20appeared%20in%20a%20published%20list%20of%20the%20top%20web%20domains%20present%20in%20the%20company's%20WebText%20training%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20class%20action%20lawsuit%20from%20the%20Author's%20Guild%2C%20two%20authors%20claimed%20that%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-copyright-lawsuit-authors-chatgpt-trained-on-books-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eused%20information%20from%20their%20books%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20train%20ChatGPT.%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyt-sues-open-ai-microsoft-alleging-trained-chatgpt-off-content-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20filed%20a%20similar%20lawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyt-sues-open-ai-microsoft-alleging-trained-chatgpt-off-content-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethe%20company%20in%20December%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20court%20documents%20in%20the%20Author's%20Guild%20lawsuit%20revealed%20that%20OpenAI%20deleted%20two%20huge%20datasets%20used%20to%20train%20GPT-3.%20Lawyers%20for%20the%20guild%20said%20the%20two%20sets%20likely%20contained%20%26quot%3Bmore%20than%20100%2C000%20published%20books.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20employees%20responsible%20for%20putting%20together%20the%20data%20no%20longer%20work%20for%20OpenAI%2C%20court%20documents%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20begun%20signing%20licensing%20agreements%20with%20news%20organizations%20to%20fairly%20use%20their%20work.%20The%20company%20has%20signed%20such%20agreements%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fai-media-lawsuits-center-for-investigative-reporting-chatgpt-mother-jones-c48452889750479410b65a119537746c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20publishers%20of%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20and%20New%20York%20Post%2C%20The%20Atlantic%2C%20Prisa%20Media%2C%20Le%20Monde%20newspaper%2C%20Financial%20Times%2C%20and%20Business%20Insider%20parent%20Axel%20Springer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20scale%20of%20content%20required%20for%20these%20bots%20to%20continuously%20learn%20will%20require%20far%20more%20than%20a%20handful%20of%20licensing%20agreements.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20solution%20is%20synthetic%20data%2C%20which%20is%20artificially%20generated%20rather%20than%20collected%20from%20the%20real%20world%2C%20and%20can%20easily%20be%20generated%20by%20machine%20learning%20algorithms.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20considered%20synthetic%20data%20as%20an%20option%20to%20train%20its%20models%2C%20but%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20has%20raised%20concerns%20about%20producing%20quality%20data.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20you%20can%20get%20over%20the%20synthetic%20data%20event%20horizon%2C%20where%20the%20model%20is%20smart%20enough%20to%20make%20good%20synthetic%20data%2C%20everything%20will%20be%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAltman%20said%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20tech%20conference%20in%20May%202023.%20The%20company%20has%20also%20explored%20a%20process%20in%20which%20AI%20models%20work%20together%20%E2%80%94%20one%20AI%20system%20produces%20data%2C%20while%20another%20judges%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20did%20not%20immediately%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-lawsuit-copyrighted-data-train-chatgpt-court-tech-ai-news-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719781766000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6681b8df1f0c1cd6d7300dee%3Ff