eauty%20standards%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%2C%20the%20couple%20has%20been%20able%20to%20expand%20the%20work%20in%20B2B%20and%20made%20their%20presence%20across%2060%20offline%20stores%20in%20Chennai%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20Goa%2C%20Ooty%2C%20and%20Coonor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20month%2C%20they%20sell%203%2C000%20fabric%20dolls.%20Last%20financial%20year%2C%20they%20clocked%20in%20a%20revenue%20of%20Rs%2075%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20glad%20that%20with%20this%20work%2C%20we%20are%20able%20to%20impart%20new%20skills%20and%20ensure%20monetary%20benefits%20for%20tribal%20women.%20The%20cycle%20is%20complete%20only%20when%20women%20start%20making%20money%20out%20of%20it%2C%20and%20do%20not%20practise%20craft%20just%20as%20a%20hobby%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20most%20of%20our%20women%20have%20increased%20their%20monthly%20incomes%20from%20Rs%202%2C000%20to%20Rs%208-10%2C000.%20Years%20back%20when%20we%20moved%20to%20the%20Nilgiris%2C%20we%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20hoped%20to%20bring%20this%20change.%20There%20is%20nothing%20more%20satisfying%20than%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sunita.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande.%20All%20photos%3A%20Suhas%20Ramegowda.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719494228000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FUntitled-design-2-1719489298.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D354515%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sunita%20and%20Suhas%20Ramegowda%20run%20'The%20Good%20Gift'%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20is%20bringing%20back%20the%20age-old%20practice%20of%20making%20rag%20dolls%20based%20around%20craft-making.%20While%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20have%20prevented%208%2C000%20kg%20of%20textile%20waste%20from%20entering%20the%20landfills%20and%20empowered%20at%20least%20200%20tribal%20women%20in%20the%20Nilgiris.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F354515%2Fthe-good-gift-fabric-rag-dolls-using-textile-waste-jobs-for-rural-tribal-women-in-nilgiris-sunita-suhas-ramegowda%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IIT-D%20Scientist%E2%80%99s%20Patented%20Tech%20Prevents%20Unwanted%20Microbial%20Growth%20in%20Water%20Tanks%2C%20Mattresses%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMuch%20before%20the%20Central%20Government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Aatmanirbhar%20Bharat%E2%80%99%20(self-reliant%20India)%20campaign%2C%20there%20was%20a%20young%20academician%20in%20New%20Delhi%20who%20lived%20by%20these%20tenets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20pursuing%20a%20PhD%20in%20polymer%20nanotechnology%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F352547%2Ffarmers-income-aneesh-jain-gram-unnati-value-chain-rajasthan-agri-startup%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(IIT)%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Dr%20Anasuya%20Roy%20decided%20to%20take%20her%20research%20beyond%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20at%20that%20point%20of%20time%20(2018-19)%2C%20was%20importing%20all%20its%20anti-microbial%20technology%20from%20other%20countries.%20When%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20dearth%20of%20brains%2C%20why%20should%20we%20be%20importing%3F%E2%80%9D%20Anasuya%20shares%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20thought%20gave%20birth%20to%20the%20entrepreneur%20inside%20the%20researcher.%20She%20decided%20to%20create%20an%20impact%20using%20her%20patented%20antimicrobial%20active%20copper%20technology.%C2%A0This%20was%20created%20along%20with%20her%20PhD%20supervisor%20Professor%20Mangala%20Joshi%20who%20is%20also%20the%20co-founder%20of%20Nanosafe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20to%20go%20about%20it%3F%20The%20answer%20to%20this%20question%20presented%20